  "prompt": "How many times has Obama met Putin?",
  "response": "Barack Obama and Vladimir Putin met numerous times during Obama's presidency from 2009 to 2017. They had formal meetings, including bilateral summits, as well as informal encounters during multilateral gatherings such as the G20 and APEC summits. Notably, some of the key meetings include:\n\n1. **2009**: Their first meeting at the G20 summit in London.\n2. **2010**: Discussions in Washington, D.C. during a nuclear security summit.\n3. **2012**: Meetings during the G20 summit in Los Cabos, Mexico.\n4. **2013**: A meeting at the G20 summit in St. Petersburg, Russia, which was significant due to the tensions over Syria.\n5. **2016**: Final meetings at the G20 summit in Hangzhou, China.\n\nIn total, Obama and Putin met at least **seven to eight times** in formal contexts during Obama's presidency. The exact count may vary slightly depending on whether one includes informal encounters, but they had a significant number of direct interactions during those years.",
